The Police, on Friday, arraigned one Lawrence Amadasun, 42, before an Ogbeson Chief Magistratesâ€™ Court in Benin City for alleged stealing of N6.2 million The defendant is being tried for a two-count charge of conspiracy and stealing. Police prosecutor, Insp. Charity Asemota alleged that the defendant committed the offence on Dec. 16, 2019. According to her, the defendant conspired with others at large and stole the sum of N6. 2 million belonging to one Mr. Moses Sunday. He said the offence contravened the provision of Sections 516 and 390(8) (b)64 of the Criminal Code Cap. 48 Vol. 11, Laws of the defunct Bendel State of Nigeria, 1976, now applicable in Edo. If found guilty of stealing, a convict stands a seven-year jail term. The defendants, however, pleaded not guilty to the two-count charge. The Chief Magistrate, Prince Mutairu Oare, admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N200,000 , with two sureties in like sum. One of the sureties must be a responsible public servant and must depose to Affidavit of Means and deposit two recent passport photographs of themselves and that of the defendant. He added that the sureties residence and place of work information must be verified by the Court Registrar. The Chief Magistrate, thereafter, adjourned the case until June 15 for further hearing. 2 men in court for stealing 20 goats in Ekiti Police arraign three men for allegedly stealing $5,000 Lagos: Cleric in court over alleged N4.3m fraud